## Security (mandatory)

- Never commit `.env`, `ÁéØÂ¢É‰ø°ÊÅØ`, API keys, SSH passwords, WeChat AppSecret, webhooks, or cert private keys
- `DEPLOY_PASSWORD`, `WECHAT_MINI_APP_SECRET`, `JWT_SECRET`, etc. come from environment only
- Use `.env.example` for shape; use `CHANGE_ME` / empty placeholders

## Stack (unchanged)

- Go API (`apps/api/`), Next.js 15 (`apps/web/`), PostgreSQL, optional WeChat mini program (`apps/miniprogram/`)
- PostgreSQL only ‚Äî no ClickHouse

## Deployment (self-host)

- Set `DEPLOY_HOST`, `DEPLOY_PASSWORD`, `APP_DOMAINS`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` before running `deploy/*.js`
- See `DEPLOYMENT.md` and `README.md` for generic install steps
- **No** automatic push to a vendor-specific production IP from this repo

## Contributing

- PRs welcome on `main`
- UI strings: `apps/web/messages/en.json` and `zh.json`
- Run `npm run test:unit` before substantial API changes

## When syncing from private

After meaningful releases in the private repo, run `sync-web-monitor-oss.js` from **that** repo so this mirror stays aligned and desensitized.
